      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MIGHTY MISS (1) broke a string of placings finishing in the money two on end before a last start fifth (23.84) at Horsham. Goes very well here finding the frame in each of three starts. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Better than the latest effort and deserves another chance. KRAKEN RIPPER (7) was strongly fancied last time but finished second (24.14), beaten a neck. The form out of the last run is proven to be strong. Well-placed to take this out. REUBEN HILL (6) missed the frame latest when sixth at Healesville (19.97) but scored four back at Warrnambool (25.55). Has a solid record from this box including two wins and a minor placing. Better than the latest run and deserves another chance. MAGIC BULLSEYE (2) won by a wide margin last start. That form reads well.",
